# try-game

This Android Studio game project (Kotlin) is a work-in-progress playable demo featuring Aama and Malsapro.

Progress
- Core game loop (SurfaceView + fixed timestep)
- Sprite loader, animated sprite support, and size normalization
- Player (Aama) with run/jump/attack
- Companion (Malsapro) with follow and ride mechanics
- Enemies with basic patrol and damage
- Particle effects on enemy hits/deaths
- Sound manager and basic SFX/background audio handling
- CI workflow that builds a debug APK

How to build & run
1. Open try-game in Android Studio.
2. Build -> Make Project. The Gradle copy task will copy sprites from the repository root into app/src/main/assets/ before compilation.
3. Run the app on a device or emulator (minSdk 21).

Debug APK (CI)
- The GitHub Actions workflow runs on pushes to try-game-initial and uploads the debug APK as an artifact named `try-game-apk`.

Notes
- Sprites and audio are bundled from the repository root; do not remove the original files (e.g., standing.png, marten-run.png, achya.mpeg) from the repo root or the build task will not find them.
- This is a demo iteration; I will continue polishing gameplay, animations, controls, and UI.
